%% Diagram: Backend lifecycle in a load balancer pool
%% Type: state
%%{init: {'htmlLabels': false}}%%
stateDiagram-v2
    [*] --> Joining
    Joining --> Healthy: passes N consecutive probes
    Healthy --> SlowStart: just promoted<br/>weight ramps from 0
    SlowStart --> Healthy: ramp window elapsed
    Healthy --> Outlier: passive signal<br/>(5xx rate, latency p99)
    Outlier --> Healthy: error budget recovered
    Healthy --> Unhealthy: fails N consecutive probes
    Unhealthy --> Healthy: passes N consecutive probes
    Healthy --> Draining: deregister / scale-in
    Outlier --> Draining: deregister
    Unhealthy --> Draining: deregister
    Draining --> [*]: drain timeout reached<br/>or in-flight = 0

    note right of SlowStart
        HAProxy: server slowstart=60s
        NGINX Plus: slow_start=60s
        Envoy: SLOW_START LB config
    end note
    note right of Outlier
        Envoy outlier detection
        AWS unhealthy_threshold + targets_health
        Used as passive complement
        to active probes.
    end note
    note right of Draining
        New requests stop.
        Existing connections finish.
        HTTP/2: GOAWAY frame (RFC 9113)
        AWS deregistration_delay default 300s.
    end note
